The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 February is 205,551 (23,691 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 January, there were 11,261 new confirmed cases (1,297.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 January, there were 10,320 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% (941 extra cases).
